text: Frastanz is a market town in the district of Feldkirch in the Austrian state of Vorarlberg. It used to be known for its production of tobacco. == History == In ancient times, Frastanz was found on a Roman Road. It was also the site of the Battle of Frastanz in 1499. == References == == Other websites == * Town of Frastanz official website Category:Settlements in Vorarlberg
